2164→\begin{proof}
2165→  \uses{def:w-localization-ideal,cor:closed-points-isom-w-local-faithfully-flat,
2166→    thm:w-localization-ideal-ind-Zariski,thm:ind-Zariski-is-ind-etale,
2167→    thm:ind-etale-comp,thm:closed-points-isom-w-local,
2168→    thm:ind-etale-plus-c-has-retraction-if-w-contractible}
2169→  \leanok
2170→  With \Cref{thm:ind-etale-plus-c-has-retraction-if-w-contractible}, it suffices to reduce to 
2171→  the case that \(B\) is furthur w-local and the closed points of \(\Spec (B)\) 
2172→  are exactly \(V(IB)\).
2173→
2174→  Let $A \to B$ be faithfully flat and ind-étale. We may replace $B$ by the ring $C = B_{w, IB}$ 
2175→  (see \Cref{def:w-localization-ideal}). To justify this, note that the map \(A \to C\) is 
2176→  faithfully flat by \Cref{cor:closed-points-isom-w-local-faithfully-flat} and \(B \to C\) is 
2177→  ind-Zariski by \Cref{thm:w-localization-ideal-ind-Zariski}, thus ind-étale by 
2178→  \Cref{thm:ind-Zariski-is-ind-etale}. Therefore, by \Cref{thm:ind-etale-comp}, the composition 
2179→  \( A \to C \) is also ind-étale. Hence, we may assume $\Spec (B)$ is w-local such that the set 
2180→  of closed points of $\Spec (B)$ is $V(IB)$ by \Cref{item:w-local-closed-points-isom-w-local,
2181→  item:inverse-image-closed-points-isom-w-local} in \Cref{thm:closed-points-isom-w-local}.
2182→
2183→  % Assume (1) or equivalently (2). We have (3)(c) by Lemma \ref{lemma:097V}. Properties (3)(a) and (3)(b) follow from Lemma \ref{lemma:09AZ}.
2184→\end{proof}
